covered: Valid Request: TC01 and TC02 validate updates with valid payloads (minimal fields and all fields).
Partial Update: TC19 demonstrates updating only the provided fields.
Non-Existing Resource: TC08 covers error for non-existent account.
Concurrency: TC17 validates concurrent PUT requests on the same account.
Authorization: TC09 tests 401 for missing/invalid authentication.
Header/Validation: TC05 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header and 400 response; Header presence is also validated in TC01/TC02.
Input Validation: TC06 (invalid accountId), TC07 (invalid data), and TC21 (invalid input formats).
Server/Network Resilience: TC12 (500 server error), TC13 (large payload), TC14 (slow network).
Data Integrity/Regression: TC15 demonstrates updating a single field (email) without overwriting others; TC20 tests min/max values.
Dependent Services: TC16 ensures propagation to a dependent service.
Security: TC18 tests mitigation of injection attacks.
Edge Scenarios: TC03/TC04 for treatNullAsReset true/false and TC22 for extra query parameters.
gaps: Partial update rejection scenario not covered (no test where partial updates are explicitly disallowed).
Caching headers for PUT responses (ETag, Cache-Control) not tested.
Non-existent resource handling: tests expect 400; 404 Not Found scenario not tested.
recommendations: Add a negative test for partial update rejection when updates are not allowed for certain fields.
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient privileges.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on PUT responses.
Consider adding a 404 Not Found test for non-existent resources or align existing tests accordingly.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify handling of bursts of PUT requests.
